^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 333 - January 27, 2003^*N
 ^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
This week's deal is one of those rare masterpieces in which the winning play for the declarer is far from obvious with all 4 hands in view, yet it would be possible for a great player to find the path to success at the table. It turned out that the actual declarer was a great player - ^*BMichel Lebel^*N of France (a former World Champion).

This week's deal took place about 3 years ago in an exhibition match where Lebel was playing with ^*BMichel Perron^*N (another of France's all-time greats). ^*BSociété Générale^*N (a French bank) sponsored a series of these matches in which the French National Team faced various local teams in an effort to help promote bridge in various parts of that country. 

This particular match was against a team from Bordeaux that included ^*BPatrice Piganeau^*N who reported this beautiful deal to me. Apparently Société Générale did a fine job in promoting this match as there were over 700(!) people watching vugraph at the playing site. The audience got to see an example of bridge at its best when this week's deal was played.

This deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.
