I will be going to Japan on February 1 to play in the ^*BNEC International Bridge Festival^*N. I am very much looking forward to this trip for a couple of reasons. First, the very first international tournament that I ever played in was in Japan in 1984 and I really enjoy visiting that fascinating country. Second, the NEC tournament has earned a reputation for being one of the toughest and best run bridge tournaments in the world. Rumor has it that the tournament organizers treat the visiting players very well (which is not a surprise given the treatment that I received when I played in Japan in 1984).

I am also pleased to report that the quarter-finals, semi-finals, and finals of the main team event at the NEC tournament (the ^*BNEC Cup^*N) will be presented as a live vugraph broadcast through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N on February 7th and 8th. I do not know the exact starting times of each session right now, but I am hopeful that this information will appear in the next ^*BDeal of the Week^*N. Starting times will also be posted in the lobby area of ^*BBridge Base Online^*N as soon as the information is known.

